<font color="#FF0000">COOKIE &amp; MTF</font><br>
<tt>Sat Nov 15  2:50:47 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Hang in there, the real Cookie! I'll call you over the weekend. Just keep it cool!<br><br>
Had a great lunch with MTF and TS. MTF wore a stylish fedora with wampum around the band, a trendy Oky lone on Range coat, a buffalo skin vest, and the cutest pair of nikes this side of the Red River. &lt;G&gt; I wore my family toga, and not to be outdone, had my sidekick AH wear red to compliment my white hair and green ostrich skin tunic. The autogyro Much Too Fast hemi blown candy apple red tang with steer horns on the hood taking two stalls with home on the range plates, being mobbed by the cutest heffers I have seem in any stockyard, was a giveaway that THE MAN was in town! My muzzle loading damascus barrel deck gun clipped his rotors in good style. They needed a shave!<br><br>
Lunch was dutch treat, but the gopher skin exchange rate in KS really screwed up the tip. No loose wampum for small change! TS is one cool dude, to have completely on your side! Hope to see him up here, soon!<br><br>
All kidding aside.<br><br>
Sitting with MTF and having some darn good conversation is one of the few times I have not felt dirty and ashamed of being a 'NamVet. I really felt proud. I hope the feeling sticks around for a while.<br><br>
Read MTF's book twice on the way back, the second time real slow. It has honesty and power. I will have to take it slow now in small chunks. There is a lot more there than meets the eye. <br><br>
OK, so I'll embarrass the hell out of MTF, but and honest book, by an honest man, with honest feelings, is an honor to read. It is a tribal book too, for out tribe of 'NamVets. It kinda made me hurt real bad, cry a lot, and feel good all over, all at the same time. MTF is a sneaky, little (?) Tunkasilla!<br><br>
I'll have more comments later, at the grave risk of having my scalp not taken, and finding my shoes filled with spiders!<br><br>
Art<br>

